  "text": "When we consider an external structure, our main concern is how to define a kernel function between arbitrary two nodes (representing two data instances) in a given graph G = (E, V ) representing the feature space. The diffusion kernel [CITATION_1] defines similarity among nodes by a diffusion process over the graph. Let us denote the Laplacian matrix of the given graph by L. Then the kernel matrix for the diffusion kernel is defined as",
